originalText.text: Pricing was reasonable and location convenient. We parked there for our cruise last week. They understandably get jammed up as passengers come in and out on Sundays. The attendant said we could take a 5 minute walk or wait 30 minutes for a valet. We had only 3 pieces of luggage and walked it. Wicked easy.

originalText.text: I went to the Wolfgang Steakhouse with my Girlfriend for my birthday last week. What we had was the Steak for Two for each of us. We went to the Wolfgang steakhouse in Time square, But we went to Tribeca restaurant. The food here is basically flawless, and it is the best steakhouse in the city. Even though it was expensive, We love the Wolfgang Steakhouse.Also they had their own parking at 16 Hubert street. The employee were very courteous. The price was very good. It was $15 dollars all day for my car to park.

originalText.text:
Just tried to park there and I was rudely told that if I can’t give an exact time that I was coming back, I couldn’t park there, despite if I called ahead of time about any schedule changes.

The guy was a real jerk about it-basically he didn’t want to have to move the car in the event that I had to pick my car up early.

So I went down the block to the icon lot-very friendly, same price, and no bs.
